(stringVal, Teach the Assistant to recognize %1$s’s face; Face Match helps the Assistant identify %1$s’s face and tell %1$s aprt from others by creating a unique model of %1$s’s face on this device.;Why set up Face Match? It allows the Assistant to proactively show %1$s %1$s’s important notifications, calendar events, reminders, and personal results if %1$s have personal results enabled.

Keep in mind: A person with similar face might be able to access %1$s’s personal results, too. You can remove Face Match permission later by turnning it off in the Assistant settings.;The Assistant uses Face Match to tell %1$s apart from others. Ask %1$s to simply approach the Google Nest Hub Max and use %1$s’s face to access messages, calendar, and other personal results.;Agree to Face Match;Here’s what you need to keep in mind;The Assistant takes photos of %1$s’s face at different angles to form a unique model of %1$s’s face, which is only stored on this Google Nest Hub Max.

If you decide later that Face Match isn’t for you, simply remove it from Assistant Settings and delete the photos of %1$s’s face on myactivity.google.com.

Note: A person with a similar face, or photos or video of %1$s’s face, might also be able to access %1$s’s personal results (calendar, reminders, etc).)
